      <bioghist id="aspace_068c704ded91bc3473e535bedd5a4d37">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Samuel Burdett Hemingway, 1886-1958: educator; A.B., Yale 1904, A.M., 1905, Ph.D., 1908; instructor in English, Yale 1908-1913, asst. prof., 1913-1926, assoc. prof., 1926-1933, prof. English, 1933-1950, prof. emeritus, 1950-1958; master of Berkeley College, 1937-1950, Master emeritus, 1950-1958.</p>
         <p>For charts outlining the genealogical relations of the Hemingway and Dimock families, please consult the<ref actuate="onrequest"
                 href="http://mssa.altfindingaids.library.yale.edu/mssa.ms.0276/mssa_ms_0276_genealogical_charts.pdf"
                 linktitle="Genealogical Charts"
                 show="new">Genealogical Charts</ref>.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ef15911493dd25358307e8a54e79dd3a">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of correspondence, financial papers, and memorabilia of the Hemingway and Hart families.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
